text: Hartmut Puls (born 25 January 1945) is a German wrestler. He competed in the men's Greco-Roman 57 kg at the 1968 Summer Olympics. ==References== Category:1945 births Category:Living people Category:German male sport wrestlers Category:Olympic wrestlers of East Germany Category:Wrestlers at the 1968 Summer Olympics Category:Sportspeople from Pomeranian Voivodeship Category:People from Chojnice
